						<summary>

						<p>Four sides of a broken stone pillar set up in the Mallikārjuna temple.</p>						

						<p>This undated inscription may be assigned to the 14th century, on the basis of palaeography.</p>						

						<p>Badly damaged and worn out. It mentions Śrīparvata and Śrī Mallikārjuna.</p>						

						</summary>
					</msContents>
